OL,3,C'A big question to live with': Would
OL,4,Cyou want to know if you could get
OL,5,Cdementia?
OL,7,FFor most people, the thought of
OL,8,Fknowing whether you'll one day develop
OL,9,Fdementia is almost unthinkable. But
OL,10,Ffor Matthew Joseph, from Holyhead in
OL,11,Fnorth Wales, it's a question that
OL,12,Fweighs on him every day.
OL,14,FDementia has haunted his family for
OL,15,Fgenerations. His mother, Jill, was
OL,16,Fdiagnosed with the condition in her
OL,17,Fearly fifties and died last year aged
OL,18,Fjust 58. Jill's mother also died of
OL,19,Fdementia and there's a strong history
OL,20,Fof the illness in the family.
