OL,3,C'A big question to live with': Would
OL,4,Cyou want to know if you could get
OL,5,Cdementia?
OL,7,F"I think from my point of view, I'd
OL,8,Frather not know," Alex said. "I don't
OL,9,Fwant it to affect our lives. I just
OL,10,Fwant to have the best time with him."
OL,12,FMatthew understands, but says he also
OL,13,Fsees the other side.
OL,15,F"There's power in knowing too," he
OL,16,Fsaid. "If someone told me I've got 20
OL,17,Fyears left before I get dementia, then
OL,18,Fat least I'd know how I want to spend
OL,19,Fthat time."
