OL,3,C'A big question to live with': Would
OL,4,Cyou want to know if you could get
OL,5,Cdementia?
OL,7,FFor now, Matthew hasn't made a
OL,8,Fdecision about testing ` but says he's
OL,9,Faware that, for families like his, the
OL,10,Ffear of dementia never really
OL,11,Fdisappears.
OL,13,FA growing challenge
OL,15,FWhile there are 982,000 people
OL,16,Fcurrently living with dementia in the
OL,17,FUK, the Alzheimers Society estimates
OL,18,Fthat more than a third of people with
OL,19,Fthe condition do not have a diagnosis.
OL,20,FThat figure is set to rise to 1.4
OL,21,Fmillion by 2040.
